<br>
Got a couple of quick questions about our pets.  I just dinged 24 a few nights ago, and have been gathering all the items for the focus items.  Well tonight I was able to get all 4 focus items.  Then I ran around and got all the spells I could, but alas I failed on every attempt on combines for the items I had.  I maxed my research at the trainer before attempting but oh well, will try again once I can get some more items.  Anyway after all the running around I gated back up to the moon to try my very first focused duel wielding earth pet(since its the only one you can buy).  <br>
<br>
Two problems:<br>
1) Pet wouldn't duel wield, I tried handing it 2 spears at the same time, then handing him one at a time, he never displayed 2 weaps, and from watching the hits he never dw'ed.<br>
<br>
2) I casted the pet holding my brand new Shovel of Ponz, when casting should I get a message from the shovel akin to other focus items??  Also the pet was the same size as the others, and his max hit seemed to be the same as what is listed here as farr as max goes, though I thought the shovel should make him hit higher??  Am I wrong about that???<br>
<br>
Am I doing something wrong?  any ideas or suggestions would be great!<br>
<br>
Thanks!<br>
Qnyin<br>
Lvl 24 Mage<br>
Terris-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uskildpade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(9/6/02 9:00:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=667.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Help please</span><hr size=1> There is NEVER a message from any of the pet focus items and at lv 24 there is no visual change in the size of the pet. You will just have to trust that they work, because they do work and help a lot.<br>
<br>
Pets can only dual wield 1h weapons, so you will have to give it two 1h weapons to do this. Summoned daggers or swords are sufficient to do this. The summoned spear is 2h. The pets should show the weapons in its hands and i have yet to see a pet change from one weapon to another if you give it a new one. The pet can, however, equip a shield AND an 2h weapon.<br>
<br>
nmee, lv 54 magician<br>
Povar Tarew Alliance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usatrekil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Satrekil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(9/6/02 2:36:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=667.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Help please</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the reply, but are you sure the spear is a 2 handed piercer.  I dont think it is.  This spell has been out alot longer then the 2hand piercing skill if my memory serves me correctly.<br>
<br>
Also what is the max a pet summoned from the lvl 24 spells should hit for.  According to the pet info here the max for the pet is 24(this is unfocused), what would be the focus max, if anyone knows?<br>
<br>
Thanks Again!!!!<br>
Qnyin<br>
